# Open Vision

## Vision 19 will be generating data for and fine-tuning its own image generation model!

In order to improve the image quality on 19, we'll be adding a 'SOTA' (state-of-the-art) operation. Currently, the SOTA model is probably between Mid-Journey and Dalle-3. Hopefully stable diffusion 3 takes the crown when it gets released 🤞

We'll be using images generated from subnet 18 for Dalle-3 and images from the SOTA operation on 19 (currently Mid-Journey) to fine-tune an Open Vision model, which will be open-sourced.

It will then be added to 19 for inference and regularly updated.

The generated data from MJ and Open Vision will also be added to the subnet 24 Omega dataset for their creation of an any-any model or for the training of an image generation model from the ground up ( 9 - Pretraining ?).

The full package will be coming to Bittensor!

## Is this not centralised?
We're trying to decentralise the centralised! To birth the best models here on Bittensor

We do have to go through APIs in order to access the model because Mid Journey has not open sourced it 😦

We're offering the ability to use multiple different APIs (imagineslash and goapi currently), and are investigating allowing you to directly use your own Discord subscription.

Furthermore, it is optional to run this model as a miner, and it will only be reflected as a very small part of the overall score.

In this update, we'll also be increasing the 'quickest response' reward from 10% extra to 20% extra to further incentivize quick responses.

## Miners
The estimated cost for miners is around $5–10 dollars a day, depending on how many other miners run it. A restart will be required if you want to run the SOTA operation.

I'll confirm which providers we will use in due time, hold fire until then before buying mega credits 😄

## Validators
There is no cost, and you will NOT require an API key. You don't have to do anything if you're running auto-updates; if you're not, you just need to do the usual restart.


# When?
The release is due on Friday at 15:00 p.m. UTC. Reg will be closed for 5 hours to reflect validators restarting.

# Vision release 3.0
**Vision 3.0 is coming...**

After all the anticipation - we're ready. Monday, 2pm UTC, Vision 3.0 will be released  🔥
I'll keep this notice brief, and detail the important info:

## Highlights
- Open source LLMs are coming to SN19 starting with the best - Mixtral 8x7b 😻
- And the latest* model from Nous Research, fine tuned on Bittensor's SN6 (*updated biweekly) 👁️
- Massively improved image quality 🔥
- New Avatar endpoint and functionality. Generate as many images of mog as you like :mog: 
- Opens the door to the biggest rollout of apps and updates Bittensor has ever seen over the coming weeks!


### Validators
In order to prepare for inference at scale we have separated the running of models (GPU) from the API inference (CPU) to allow scalability to not impact deliverability.
 
- A100/H100 GPU (80GB is what's important) will be required. 
- A super simple one-click docker template has been created to take care of the entire install and setup process and running of this server. 
- You will also need a CPU server to run your API proxy and hold your key 
Both are required regardless of whether you run synthetic or organic queries.

### Miners
Mining has been optimised for scaling in the exact same way as validating, meaning you now require:

- A CPU server to run the API proxy, which is where your key will live. You can run multiple miners on the same CPU.
- Worker server(s) For the initial release, there are the following tasks
-- LLM for Mixtral-8x7b (advised A100/H100) [multiple miners can potentially share depending on load]
-- LLM for Latest bittensor fine-tune (advised A100/H100) [multiple miners can potentially share depending on load]
-- 9x Image generation tasks (3x text to image, 3x image to image, 1x in-paint, 1x clip embeddings, 1x upscale, 1x avatar generation). All of these can be run a single 4090, but A100 Advised for quicker generation

It's up to you how many you want to support!

**TESTNET code will be released tomorrow** 
I will open a channel just for any dedicated miners and validators who want to test over the weekend before release!

Any mining questions will be best answered in there, I'll be around all weekend for 15hr a day support (mans gotta sleep).
